@sowmyaramesh To follow up with our talk, our current CLI framework doesn't check whether an option is used in a command or not, i.e. they are all optional. In other words, whether I add an option or not doesn't change your extension repository results, if you don't use these options. For example, "bin/falcon extension -enumerate -url http://localhost:15000 -d -ddd " gives the same result as "bin/falcon extension -enumerate -url http://localhost:15000".

This resembles with REST api design, i.e. it won't throw error if user pass an unrecognized parameter. Hope this resolves your concern.

If you want to be able to throw error for unsupported options, you need to change our CLI framework.

@vrangan I have tried to build the Falcon with the patch in pull request. When I use "mvn clean install" build fails in examples module. It looks like that testng dependency is required explicitly now.

`[ERROR] Failed to execute goal org.apache.maven.plugins:maven-surefire-plugin:2.16:test (default-test) on project falcon-examples: groups/excludedGroups require TestNG or JUnit48+ on project test classpath -> [Help 1]`

But when I use "mvn clean install -Ptest-patch", build succeeds . Earlier also it succeeded by using hadoop-2 profile.
